## Results

Direct edge-return readout:

| Split | Direction | Pairwise Rank | Best Asset | Correlation | MAE | RMSE |
| --- | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: |
| train `[0,730)` | 0.499872 | 0.519334 | 0.342071 | -0.00121821 | 0.0235174 | 0.0329349 |
| eval `[760,1088)` | 0.510840 | 0.557249 | 0.388211 | 0.00546659 | 0.0221558 | 0.0279358 |

The original node-potential edge projection in the same eval report stayed near
random:

```text
eval.edge_return_projection_directional_accuracy = 0.499322
eval.edge_return_projection_pairwise_rank_accuracy = 0.467818
eval.edge_return_projection_best_asset_agreement = 0.298780
eval.edge_return_projection_correlation = 0.00583662
```

The direct head improves eval pairwise rank and best-asset agreement slightly
relative to the projection path, but not enough to change the diagnosis. It is
well below the deterministic benchmark gate:

```text
MIN_ORACLE_EDGE_RETURN_DIRECTIONAL_ACCURACY = 0.95
MIN_ORACLE_EDGE_RETURN_PAIRWISE_RANK_ACCURACY = 0.95
MIN_ORACLE_EDGE_RETURN_BEST_ASSET_AGREEMENT = 0.60
```

## Interpretation

This test closes one important hypothesis:

```text
The failure is not only that edge return was a weak auxiliary projection on the
node-potential expected value. A dedicated edge-return readout head also fails
to learn useful train-range direction/rank from the current MDN context.
```

The frozen-representation supervised probe remains the comparison point:

```text
frozen_representation.eval.directional_accuracy = 0.738482384824
frozen_representation.eval.pairwise_rank_accuracy = 0.707994579946
frozen_representation.eval.best_asset_agreement = 0.597560975610
frozen_representation.eval.correlation = 0.622333108679
```

So useful edge signal exists in the representation probe, but the current MDN
context/readout/training path does not extract it. The next diagnostic should
isolate the signal path more directly:

```text
synthetic_signal_path_isolation.v1
```

That diagnostic should compare raw target transform, phase/lag oracle, frozen
representation linear/MLP probes, and the MDN direct readout on the same
train/eval ranges before returning to PPO tuning.
